  "base_commit": "f0fb819fad23d576f4bb9c6c182166849b0b9a7b",
  "pr_number": 6784,
  "issue_number": 6777,
  "issue_title": "feat: limit batch size on serverside",
  "issue_body": "### Describe the feature you'd like to request\n\nif in my server i enable batching someone can send batch of 1000 operations. which could be very bad for my server. with traditional one request being one request, one can build/use rate limiting in infra level, which can't quite work well when one request actually contains 1000 sub requests. \n\nI think this creates big security risk on anyone who serves trpc server with batch enabled in prod. \n\n### Describe the solution you'd like to see\n\nWe should be able to set sensible batch size limit in server, as of now, afaik we can set the limit in client but not on server. and most important part is ability to set this limit on server. \n\n### Describe alternate solutions\n\nIn create context function do this::\n```ts\nconst queryPath = req.url?.split(\"?\")[0] ?? \"\";\nconst tprcPrefix = \"/api/trpc/\";\n\nif (!queryPath.startsWith(tprcPrefix)) {\n  // in case we move mount tprc on different path we want to fail loudly\n  throw new Error(\"trpc prefix is outdated\");\n}\nconst batchSize = queryPath.split(\",\").length;\n\nif (batchSize > 20) {\n  throw new TRPCError({\n    code: \"BAD_REQUEST\",\n    message: `Batch size of ${batchSize.toString()} is not allowed`,\n  });\n}\n```\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_\n\n### \ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc67\u200d\ud83d\udc66 Contributing\n\n- [ ] \ud83d\ude4b\u200d\u2642\ufe0f Yes, I'd be down to file a PR implementing this feature!",
  "merged_at": "2025-05-26T14:17:50Z",
  "test_cmd": [
    "npm",
    "test"
  ],
